Recommendations:
2.5    We recommended and Management agreed:
to consider creating a Road Inventory Committee (RIC) as mandated in the DILG’s Local Road Asset Management for LGUs Manual;
that the RIC timely conduct an annual physical inventory count of road networks to allow sufficient time for reconciliation with the accounting records;
that the RIC ensure the preparation and timely submission of the required RPCLRN to the Office of the Auditor  and to the MACCO for subsequent reconciliation with the local road network property cards;
that the MGSO, MEO, and MACCO evaluate the existing processes in the identification of roads that qualify as PPE; to reconcile inventory records of both; and perform the duties and responsibilities articulated under COA Circular 2015-008 to properly account for local road networks; and
that the Municipal Accounting Office make the necessary adjustments, if necessary, to ensure that the Road Networks and its corresponding Accumulated Depreciation accounts are accurate; and to submit the adjustments made to the Audit Team.

Recommendations:
3.6    We recommended and Management agreed:
that the MGSO conduct physical count of these inventory accounts to concerned offices to ensure whether these items still exist;
that the MACCO prepare adjusting entries after a reconciliation of its records with the MGSO;
to conduct an extensive verification, analysis, and validation of the dormant accounts;
to file a request for authority to write off dormant accounts, duly supported with the documents enumerated in Section 8 of COA Circular 2023-008 before the Office of the Auditor; and
to consider creating a separate Inventory Committee for goods and supplies responsible for the planning, the conduct of physical count, and the preparation of report thereon.

Recommendations:
5.10  We recommended and Management agreed to:
compel the Punong Barangays to submit their final project proposals as early as the first quarter of the preceding year, allowing sufficient time for any required adjustments in response to significant events that could impact the timely implementation of the projects;
conduct timely and proper validation of identified or proposed projects to ensure that only feasible and well-planned and procurement-and-implementation-ready PPAs, thus free from any issues of ownership and right-of-way or boundary issues, are included in the AIP;
ensure timely finalization and approval of AIP (on or before June 7 of every preceding year as per Section 10.3.3 of DILG-NEDA-DBM-DOF Joint Memorandum Circular No. 1 dated November 18, 2016); and
strengthen the monitoring of the implementation of the projects to ensure timely implementation and completion of projects.

Recommendations:
We recommended and Management agreed to:
Grant additional cash advances only when the previous ones were already settled and/or liquidated;
Submit the liquidation of the cash advances for CF within the required timeframe, to comply with the Joint Circular;
Entrust to other personnel the liquidation of the CF to preclude delays in the submission of liquidation; and
Strictly comply with the general guidelines in the release, use, and liquidation of confidential fund.

Recommendations:
We recommended to Management the following:
For the Municipal Planning and Development Officer and Municipal Engineer: to collaborate in closely monitoring the implementation of projects funded under the BDP of the Municipality as mandated in Section 6 of DBM-DOF-DILG Joint Memorandum Circular No. 1 dated November 4, 2020;
For the Local Chief Executive: to oblige the concerned municipal personnel to give monthly/quarterly reports during Management Meeting of the LGU on the updates on the status of implementation of projects under the Barangay Development Program so as to create appropriate strategies to hasten the implementation of these projects;
For the Municipal Development Council: to evaluate if the scheme of transferring funds to the barangays and leaving the implementation stage into their hands is effective and efficient so as to deliver significant socio-economic developments that could positively impact the welfare of its constituents had all the projects been completed on time; and
For the Municipal Accountant: to issue demand letters to the barangays concerned to immediately liquidate the fund transfers and to ensure completeness of supporting documents required for the liquidation of these fund transfers granted under the Barangay Development Program of the Municipality (both for CY 2023 & prior years).
